<li><a href="resources.html">Links and resources</a></li>

<p>
Hi, I'm Theo, and welcome to my home page. I am a lecturer in Biometry at <a href="http://www.sun.ac.za/">Stellenbosch University</a>, researcher, applied statistician, and all-round data analyst.<br>
<br>
I am passionate about <a href="http://www.r-project.org/">statistical computing</a>, <a href="http://www.fsf.org/">free software</a> and machine learning, amongst other things. My current research interests are in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multivariate_statistics">multivariate statistics</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principal_component_analysis">principal component analysis (PCA)</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bootstrapping_(statistics)">bootstrap</a> and other <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resampling_(statistics)">resampling</a> methods, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonparametric_statistics">non-parametric statistics</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biostatistics">biostatistics</a>.<br>
<br>
You can contact me via <a href="http://za.linkedin.com/in/theopepler/">LinkedIn</a>, or by email. My address is tpepler, followed by the "at" sign, followed by the word, sun. After that, you write dot ac dot za.

<br><br><br><br>

<b>P.T. Pepler</b><br>
Stellenbosch University<br>
